"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514128","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-04-26","<p>I sympathise with the anguish caused to the families of victims where the offender wilfully refuses to disclose the whereabouts of their loved one. Such behaviour is already taken into account by the court when sentencing the offender, and by the independent Parole Board when assessing an offender’s continuing risk for the purposes of deciding whether he or she is eligible for possible release. The Parole Board has at my request, however, agreed to review its guidance on this particular issue as part of a review of all its guidance in 2016.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-04-26T10:53:15.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514128/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514128/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514128/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-04-19","Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the potential benefits of proposals to deny parole or release to people incarcerated for charges of murder for as long as they refuse to disclose the whereabouts of their victim's remains.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","34592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514129","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-04-26","<p>The Secretary of State for Justice attended public meetings of the Justice Select Committee on two occasions since his appointment. The dates on which he attended was 15 July 2015 and 16 March 2016.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-04-26T10:48:55.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514129/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514129/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514129/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-04-19","Justice Select Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many times he has attended public meetings of the Justice Committee since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","34564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514130","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-04-25","<p>The Government is disappointed with the decision of the Supreme Court in the judicial review of the civil legal aid residence test. We will now wait for the full written judgement to consider.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>To date, the Ministry of Justice has spent £152,196.50 (excluding VAT) in legal fees in proceedings in the High Court, the Court of Appeal and the Supreme Court in <em>Public Law Project v The Lord Chancellor</em>.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-04-25T15:05:50.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514130/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514130/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514130/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-04-19","Legal Aid Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much the Government has spent during Public Law Project v The Lord Chancellor [2015] EWCA Civ 1193, 25 November 2015.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","34548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514131","Leader of the House","false","2016-04-25","<p>The Joint Committee on the Palace of Westminster, co-chaired by the Leader of the House of Commons and the Leader of the House of Lords, was established on 16 and 20 July 2015 to examine the restoration and renewal of the Palace of Westminster. The Committee is considering evidence from a wide range of experts, Parliamentarians and stakeholders and will report in due course.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2016-04-25T14:20:54.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514131/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514131/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514131/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2016-04-19","Palace of Westminster: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what progress has been made on plans for the complete renovation of the Palace of Westminster; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","34544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514132","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-27","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills believes that the General Product Safety Regulations should ensure that lasers used by driverless cars do not present an unacceptable health risk.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-27T14:15:27.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514132/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514132/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514132/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-19","Driverless Vehicles: Lasers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 April 2016 to Question 33237, what assessment his Department has made of the potential health risks of the use of lasers by driverless vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","34542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514133","Department for Transport","false","2016-04-27","<p>Attendance at Committee meetings is a matter of public record. Transcripts of appearances can be found in Hansard and on Committee web pages.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-04-27T14:34:06.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514133/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514133/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514133/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-04-19","Transport Select Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many times he has attended public meetings of the Transport Committee since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","34563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514134","Department for Transport","false","2016-04-27","<p>Drivers can retain their entitlement to drive while medical investigations are ongoing, providing the licence has not been previously withdrawn on medical grounds and the driver is not a risk to road safety. Drivers are advised to check with their doctor or DVLA if they are unsure whether they should continue driving while their fitness to drive is being assessed.</p><p> </p><p>Information about driving while waiting for an application to be processed is included on the driving licence application form.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-04-27T15:08:33.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514134/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514134/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514134/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-04-19","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on whether drivers who are waiting for medical tests to confirm whether they are safe to drive should retain their licence in the meantime.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","34604"
