"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513682","Department of Health","false","2016-04-26","<p>We are committed to improving the oral health of school children. Public Health England (PHE) has produced a toolkit to support local authorities in their responsibility to improve dental health and reduce inequalities among children and young people in their area. It supports local authorities to invest in programmes which have demonstrated improvement in children’s dental health, for example targeted community-based fluoride varnish programmes, targeted tooth brushing programmes and water fluoridation. PHE has also this year published a toolkit to support the consideration of water fluoridation as a measure to reduce levels of tooth decay.</p><p>Sugar consumption is the primary cause of tooth decay in children. The Sugar Swaps campaign was launched in January 2015, helping families reduce their sugar consumption through making simple swaps to their diets. In addition PHE has developed guidance for dental teams on preventing dental disease in young children. Advice on prevention of dental disease has also been published by the National Institute of Health and Care Excellence.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-04-26T10:28:30.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513682/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513682/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513682/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-18","Dental Health: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to improve dental standards amongst primary school age children.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","34516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513683","Department of Health","false","2016-04-21","<p>The Department is concerned about the current situation at Chorley and South Ribble Hospital and is actively monitoring developments. These matters, including recruitment, are for Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust as employer, and NHS Improvement as regulator. The Trust has not asked the Department for any support in resolving these issues.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-04-21T10:31:00.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513683/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513683/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513683/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-04-18","Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans his Department has to work with Lancashire Teaching Hospitals Trust following the closure of Chorley Accident and Emergency unit.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","34509"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513684","Home Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>The Aircraft Accident investigation Bureau investigation into the collision will be made public. However, the separate, ongoing criminal investigation, and any decision to release the results of the investigation, is an operational matter for the Metropolitan Police, as the investigatory authority.</p><p>Guidance has been circulated to Police Forces to assist them when dealing with incidents involving misuse. A decision on whether to investigate and prosecute is made on an assessment of threat, risk and harm.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","34359","2016-04-27T14:19:36.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513684/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513684/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513684/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513684/answer/previousversion/56594","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-18","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will ensure that the results of the police investigation into the drone collision at Heathrow airport on 17 April 2016 are published.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","34467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513685","Home Office","false","2016-04-21","<p>Exit checks were introduced on 8 April 2015. My Department is considering the use of exit checks data for statistical reporting purposes and plans to publish an initial evaluation of the use of exit checks for this purpose on 26 May. Any data published then will be subject to data assurance standards.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-04-21T11:59:39.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513685/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513685/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513685/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-18","Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the proportion is of (a) international students and (b) other migrants whose entry clearance visa or extension of stay has expired at the point at which they exit the UK.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","34470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513686","Home Office","false","2016-04-21","<p>The deployment of officers by police forces in England and Wales under mutual aid arrangements is an operational matter for those forces.</p><p>The Home Office does not routinely collect the requested information.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-04-21T11:54:50.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513686/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513686/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/513686/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-18","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many requests have been made by police forces for mutual aid in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jack Dromey","Birmingham, Erdington","Jack Dromey","34425"
